ass="fonetic text-style-alt">un-yun</span><p>Onions are endlessly versatile and an essential ingredient in countless recipes. Native to Asia…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="large bunch parsley">large bunch <a href="/glossary/parsley" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--2 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">parsley</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--2"><article id="node-259636" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/parsley"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/parsley.jpg?itok=ZJpglKu3" width="100" height="100" alt="Parsley" title="The traditional British choice is curly parsley, but flat leaved (Continental) parsley is also widely available" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/parsley">Parsley</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">par-slee</span><p>One of the most ubiquitous herbs in British cookery, parsley is also popular in European and…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="6 young carrots, scrubbed and left whole">6 young <a href="/glossary/carrot" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--3 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">carrots</a>, scrubbed and left whole<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--3"><article id="node-257862" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/carrot"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/carrot_0.jpg?itok=8HZdtP_H" width="100" height="100" alt="Carrot" title="Carrot" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/carrot">Carrot</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">ka-rot</span><p>The carrot, with its distinctive bright orange colour, is one of the most versatile root…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="6 small leeks">6 small <a href="/glossary/leek" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--4 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">leeks</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--4"><article id="node-252091" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/leek"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/leek.jpg?itok=hwQbd109" width="100" height="100" alt="Leeks" title="Like garlic and onion, leeks are a member of the allium family, but have their own distinct flavour" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/leek">Leek</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">lee-k</span><p>Like garlic and onion, leeks are a member of the allium family, but have their own distinct…</p> </article></span></li></ul><h3 class="ingredients-list__group-title">For the relish</h3><ul class="ingredients-list__group"><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="3 large homecooked beetroot, coarsely grated">3 large homecooked <a href="/glossary/beetroot" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--5 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">beetroot</a>, coarsely grated<span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--5"><article id="node-252121" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/beetroot"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/beetroot.jpg?itok=puc7kKJD" width="100" height="100" alt="Beetroot" title="Beetroot is a root vegetable with dark, purple skin and pink/purple flesh" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/beetroot">Beetroot</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">beat-root</span><p>A favourite in 1970's British salads (served cooked and pickled in vinegar), beetroot is a…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="3 tbsp freshly grated horseradish">3 tbsp freshly grated <a href="/glossary/horse-radish" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--6 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">horseradish</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--6"><article id="node-6909541" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/horse-radish"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary-item/glossary-image/2017/11/horseradish-root.jpg?itok=yjxynaCi" width="100" height="100" alt="Horseradish root on a wooden chopping board" title="Horseradish" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/horse-radish">Horseradish</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">hors rad-ish</span><p>Horseradish root is larger than an ordinary radish, and has a hot, peppery flavour.</p><p>It…</p> </article></span></li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 tsp golden caster sugar">2 tsp golden caster sugar</li><li class="ingredients-list__item" itemprop="ingredients" content="2 tbsp balsamic vinegar">2 tbsp <a href="/glossary/balsamic-vinegar" class="ingredients-list__glossary-link" data-tooltip-content="#ingredients-glossary--7 &gt; article" data-tooltip-width="350" data-tooltip-hide-delay="200" data-tooltip-flyout="true">balsamic vinegar</a><span class="ingredients-list__glossary-element" id="ingredients-glossary--7"><article id="node-259681" role="main" class="node node-glossary-item node-teaser node-teaser clearfix main row grid-padding"><div class="node-image"> <a href="/glossary/balsamic-vinegar"><img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/bbcgf_thumbnail_search/public/glossary/balsamic.jpg?itok=qzU_RWSK" width="100" height="100" alt="Balsamic vinegar" title="For the real deal, always look for the trems tradizionale/DOC or aceto balsamico di Modena" /></a></div><h2 class="node-title node-glossary-title"><a href="/glossary/balsamic-vinegar">Balsamic vinegar</a></h2> <span class="fonetic text-style-alt">bal-sam-ick vin-ee-gah</span><p>True Balsamic vinegar is an artisan product from Modena, in Emilia Romagna, Italy, and is made…</p> </article></span></li></ul></div></div> </section> <section id="recipe-method" class="responsive-tabs__pane"><h2 class="responsive-tabs__pane-title">Method</h2><div class="method"><ol class="method__list"><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>Put the beef in a pan that is big enough to fit it and all the vegetables. Cover it with water and bring to the boil, skimming off the froth that comes to the surface. Tip the onion and parsley into the pot and simmer gently for 1 hr, skimming as necessary. Add the carrots and simmer for 30 mins. Finally, add the leeks and simmer for 30 mins longer. The meat is ready when it feels tender when prodded with a fork.</p></li><li class="method__item" itemprop="recipeInstructions"><p>While the meat cooks, mix the beetroot and horseradish with the sugar and vinegar until the sugar has dissolved. remove the beef and place it on a board. Scoop out the carrots and leeks into a serving dish. Slice the beef at the table and serve with the vegetables and beetroot relish – but warn everyone that a little goes a long way! You can also offer some cooking liquid to drizzle over if anyone wants it.</p></li></ol></div> <footer class="recipe-info"><div class="recipe-info__publication">Recipe from Good Food magazine, <a href="/search/recipes/date/1220223600" class="text-style-alt">September 2008</a></div> <a class="recipe-info__magazine-ad" href=" https://www.buysubscriptions.com/print/bbc-good-food-magazine-subscription?promo=GFBS718&style=Brand&utm_medium=brandsite&utm_source=bbcgoodfood.com&utm_campaign=recipe_GFBS718_Brand&utm_content=recipe-banner" rel="external" onclick="Drupal.GFAnalytics.trackEvent(['Magazines', 'subscribe', 'Recipe' ])"> <img src="https://www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/magazine/gf_aug18_337x109.jpg" alt="BBC GoodFood Magazine" /> </a> </footer> </section></div></div> <section id="block-bbcgf-search-views-bbcgf-cc-rel-recipes" class="section-box section-box--you-may-also-like"> <header class="section-box__header"><h2 class="section-box__title">You may also like</h2> </header><div class="section-box__content"><div class="carousel"><div class="flexslider type-1" data-type="1"><ul class="slides"><li class=""><article id="node-4894741" class="node node-recipe node-carousel-slide-narrow clearfix"><div class="vertical-push-item__image"> <img src="//www.bbcgoodfood.com/sites/default/files/styles/carousel_small/public/recipe_images/blood-orange-chilli-marmalade.jpg?itok=OONESCi0" width="324" height="294" alt="Blood orange &amp; chilli marmalade" title="Blood orange &amp; chilli marmalade" /></div><h3 class="vertical-push-item__title"> <a href="/recipes/blood-orange-chilli-marmalade"> Blood orange &amp; chilli marmalade </a></h3><div class="push-item__ratings"><div class="clearfix fivestar-average-stars fivestar-average-